				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">wow. so much anger.
<br />

<br />
yes, shamans need fixing and balancing. 
<br />

<br />
yes, FA should last longer, but as long as the people i'm keeping it on don't whine if it wears off while i'm doing other things, i really don't mind.
<br />

<br />
yes, our "CH" is laughable, and that's sad. i'd say that druids shouldn't be able to outheal us, but well, it's fine with me if they can. i don't want to have to heal. that's just personal preference, though. they certainly shouldn't be able to outheal us they way that they do now. 
<br />

<br />
yes, i'd like to have buffs that people really wanted, beside focus, which isn't really all that great anyhow. the people that i play with still benefit from my stat buffs, but it won't be much longer before most of them don't anymore. i can't remember the last time i cast diaku, for example. 
<br />

<br />
yes, my dots have a ridiculous amount of aggro.  mostly, though, i can avoid getting hit if i want to. and yes, i 
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">can</span> and frequently <span style="font-style: italic">do</span> stack several on a raid encounter mob, keep them on, and not get summoned and killed 4 out of 5 times, unless the tank should die first, in which case i'm likely to be shammypaste very quickly. *shrug* i can deal with that. it's not any more likely to make me shammypaste than slowing and or crippling will, in my experience. i play with sehra, i die a lot, it's fun, i'm happy. 
<br />

<br />
yes, i can and do use my aggro issues to my advantage, for example (as sehra said), tanking in groups with less than 'ideal' makeup. is it the most efficient thing that i could be doing? well, it depends on who else is there, and what needs to be done. i'm not going to be a class snob and refuse to join a group because there isn't a tank, or a cleric, or a druid, or a chanter, or whatever. as a shaman, i am by nature flexible, and will fill whatever role i am required to. that is the strength that seh was speaking about, the ability to take a disadvantage (in this instance dot and debuff aggro), and to find a way to use it to my (and my group's) advantage. 
<br />

